{
  "name": "RPlog_Fire_y_tempers_in_the_Burn_Ward",
  "title": "Fiery Tempers in the Burn Ward",
  "summary": "In a sterile private room of Coronet City's Lady of the Lake Hospital, the New Republic ambassador Ambrosia Delgard recuperates from horrific burns suffered when her diplomatic convoy on Tatooine was destroyed. Commander Argon Brand of the New Republic Navy arrives to investigate, soon joined by Teag Barrett, a smooth corporate functionary sent in place of his employer Ewan Dain, whom Ambrosia bitterly blames for the slaughter of her escort and her delivery into a bounty hunter's hands. Teag plays a holographic recording of Dain's exculpatory account, which Ambrosia furiously denounces as a lie before recounting her own searing memory of the ambush, the death of her aide Merk, and her abduction by the Trandoshan hunter Nachkt. The marine Lieutenant Halos shoulders her way in with flowers and blunt affection, and finally Dain himself appears with bodyguards to plead his innocence, insisting he killed none of her people and only tried to save her. Worn down rather than appeased, Ambrosia grudgingly deems his account plausible and extracts his promise to file a full written statement to NRI, including all he knows of Nachkt of clan Voth, before sending him off and turning her face back to the shaded window.",
